The duo were awarded for their outstanding performances in athletics that have helped cement Kenya’s sports prowess in the world.In 2008, Ndereba was described by Chicago Tribune sportswriter Philip Hersh as the greatest women's marathoner of all time having won two Olympic silver medals.   Kenya's legendary long-distance runner Catherine 'The Great' Ndereba and reigning world 1,500m champion Timothy Cheruiyot were among Kenyans feted by President Uhuru Kenyatta during the Jamhuri Day celebrations at the Nyayo National Stadium on Saturday.
The duo were awarded for their outstanding performances in athletics that have helped cement Kenya’s sports prowess in the world.  



